    {
      "id": "n20",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 19,
      "level": 2,
      "text": "What the Goethe B2 Exam Checks"
    },
    {
      "id": "n21",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 20,
      "text": "Goethe-Zertifikat B2 confirms advanced German skills at CEFR B2 for young people and adults."
    },
    {
      "id": "n22",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 21,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Exam format and timing"
    },
    {
      "id": "n23",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 22,
      "text": "The exam has listening, reading, writing, and speaking modules. The four modules can be taken individually or in combination."
    },
    {
      "id": "n24",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 23,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Listening"
    },
    {
      "id": "n25",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 24,
      "text": "40 minutes"
    },
    {
      "id": "n26",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 25,
      "text": "Interviews, lectures, conversations, everyday statements, and radio material."
    },
    {
      "id": "n27",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 26,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Reading"
    },
    {
      "id": "n28",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 27,
      "text": "65 minutes"
    },
    {
      "id": "n29",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 28,
      "text": "Forum posts, newspaper and magazine articles, comments, and regulations."
    },
    {
      "id": "n30",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 29,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Writing"
    },
    {
      "id": "n31",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 30,
      "text": "75 minutes"
    },
    {
      "id": "n32",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 31,
      "text": "A written forum opinion on a current social issue and a formal professional message."
    },
    {
      "id": "n33",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 32,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Speaking"
    },
    {
      "id": "n34",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 33,
      "text": "15 minutes"
    },
    {
      "id": "n35",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 34,
      "text": "A short talk on a given topic, follow-up conversation, and argument exchange."
    },
    {
      "id": "n36",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 35,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Best for"
    },
    {
      "id": "n37",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 36,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "Advanced work and study preparation"
    },
    {
      "id": "n38",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 37,
      "text": "Useful for job applications, Ausbildung preparation, medical-field preparation, and more complex German communication."
    },
    {
      "id": "n39",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 38,
      "level": 4,
      "text": "University route research"
    },
    {
      "id": "n40",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 39,
      "text": "Some universities accept Goethe B2, but many German-taught programs require C1/C2 or a specific university-approved exam."
    },
    {
      "id": "n41",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 40,
      "level": 3,
      "text": "How to use your practice time"
    },
    {
      "id": "n42",
      "type": "list",
      "order": 41,
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Extracting main points and details from longer, more abstract input."
        },
        {
          "text": "Building arguments with advantages, disadvantages, examples, and clear transitions."
        },
        {
          "text": "Speaking feedback for short talks, follow-up answers, and discussions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "n43",
      "type": "heading",
      "order": 42,
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Frequently Asked Questions"
    },
    {
      "id": "n44",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 43,
      "text": "Everything you need to know about the exam!"
    },
    {
      "id": "n45",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 44,
      "text": "Some universities accept Goethe B2, but it depends on the program. Many German-taught programs ask for C1/C2, DSH, TestDaF, or another listed proof."
    },
    {
      "id": "n46",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 45,
      "text": "Yes. B2 is useful for proving advanced German in job applications and for more independent professional communication."
    },
    {
      "id": "n47",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 46,
      "text": "Argument structure, formal writing, longer listening, viewpoint-heavy reading, and speaking with examples and counterpoints."
    },
    {
      "id": "n48",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "order": 47,
      "text": "Last reviewed: May 2026. This page is independent exam preparation. For official registration, fees, dates, and accepted certificate rules, check the exam provider and the institution or authority requesting your certificate."
    }
